<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2007/06/01/spring-framework-2-1-m2-released">Spring Framework 2.1 M2 Released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/ba9686d8c567aabedc1b7f8b6a7fb3d6?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/jhoeller">Juergen Hoeller</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2007-06-01 03:44:00.0">June 1, 2007</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="990" href="/blog/2007/06/01/spring-framework-2-1-m2-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Dear Spring Community, </p>
<p align="left">I’m pleased to announce that Spring 2.1 M2 has been released! <br> <br>This is the second milestone release in the Spring 2.1 series, introducing refinements in the annotation config support as well as support for AspectJ load-time weaving and various further new features.</p>
<p align="left">This release also introduces a revised structure for Spring’s module jars, now prepared for OSGi. Note that Hibernate 2.1 support has been dropped: Spring generally requires Hibernate 3.1 or higher now.&nbsp; <br></p>
<p align="center"><img border="0" title="Spring 2.1 M1 Released" alt="Spring 2.1 M1 Released" src="http://static.springframework.org/images/spring21.png"></p>
<div align="center">
<a href="https://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=73357&amp;package_id=173644&amp;release_id=512511" target="_blank">Download</a> |
<a href="http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.1.0-m2/reference/index.html" target="_blank">Documentation</a> |
<a href="http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.1.0-m2/changelog.txt" target="_blank">Changelog</a>&nbsp;
</div>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2007/06/01/spring-framework-2-1-m2-released">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
